Christopher A. (Chris) Halmy 

		
		CFO, 

	
		 Ally Financial Inc. (Formerly known as GMAC Financial Services) 	

 
Last Updated: 12/30/2016 



Executive Summary
Chris Halmy received both his BS in Accounting and MBA from Catholic university Villanova. He went on to hold treasury, finance and accounting positions at MBNA America, Merrill Lynch, JP Morgan, and Deloitte and Touche. Halmy joined Bank of America in 1997 as a global funding executive responsible for funding and liquidity activi 
Personal Attributes and Interests

He served as an adjunct professor at Wesley College from 1999 to 2006.
Halmy currently serves as an adjunct professor at Queens University. 
Current Focus

Overview: Ally Financial Inc. is a leading automotive financial services company powered by a top direct banking franchise. Ally's automotive services business offers a full spectrum of financial products and servic 
Biographical Highlights

Halmy was born on September 15, 1968.
He holds BS in Accounting and an MBA from Villanova University. 
 





